message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper discusses techniques for improving a domain-agnostic question answering model, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of large pre-trained language models and data sampling strategies also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions back-translation, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and machine translation (MT), indicating cs.IR as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of XLNet, a neural network architecture, suggests a focus on neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE a possible sub-category as well.
